42 // When making *any* change here, bump minor
43 // If the change is incompatible, then bump major and set minor to 0
44 // This ensures WALLET_RPC_VERSION always increases, that every change
45 // has its own version, and that clients can just test major to see
46 // whether they can talk to a given wallet without having to know in
47 // advance which version they will stop working with
48 // Don't go over 32767 for any of these
49 #define WALLET_RPC_VERSION_MAJOR 1
50 #define WALLET_RPC_VERSION_MINOR 17
51 #define MAKE_WALLET_RPC_VERSION(major,minor) (((major)<<16)|(minor))
52 #define WALLET_RPC_VERSION MAKE_WALLET_RPC_VERSION(WALLET_RPC_VERSION_MAJOR, WALLET_RPC_VERSION_MINOR)
53

55 #define WALLET_RPC_STATUS_BUSY "BUSY"

74  namespace {
78  template <size_t... N>
79  constexpr std::array<std::string_view, sizeof...(N)> NAMES(const char (&...names)[N]) {
80  static_assert(sizeof...(N) > 0, "RPC command must have at least one name");
81  return {std::string_view{names, N-1}...};
82  }
83  }

87  // Return the wallet's balance.
88  struct GET_BALANCE : RPC_COMMAND
89  {
90  static constexpr auto names() { return NAMES("get_balance", "getbalance"); }
91 
92  struct request
93  {
94  uint32_t account_index; // Return balance for this account.
95  std::set<uint32_t> address_indices; // (Optional) Return balance detail for those subaddresses.
96  bool all_accounts; // If true, return balance for all accounts, subaddr_indices and account_index are ignored
97  bool strict; // If true, only return the balance for transactions that have been spent and are not pending (i.e. excluding any transactions sitting in the TX pool)
98 
99  KV_MAP_SERIALIZABLE
100  };
101 
102  struct per_subaddress_info
103  {
104  uint32_t account_index; // Index of the account in the wallet.
105  uint32_t address_index; // Index of the subaddress in the account.
106  std::string address; // Address at this index. Base58 representation of the public keys.
107  uint64_t balance; // Balance for the subaddress (locked or unlocked).
108  uint64_t unlocked_balance; // Unlocked funds are those funds that are sufficiently deep enough in the oxen blockchain to be considered safe to spend.
109  std::string label; // Label for the subaddress.
110  uint64_t num_unspent_outputs; // Number of unspent outputs available for the subaddress.
111  uint64_t blocks_to_unlock; // The number of blocks remaining for the balance to unlock
112  uint64_t time_to_unlock; // Timestamp of expected unlock
113 
114  KV_MAP_SERIALIZABLE
115  };
116 
117  struct response
118  {
119  uint64_t balance; // The total balance (atomic units) of the currently opened wallet.
120  uint64_t unlocked_balance; // Unlocked funds are those funds that are sufficiently deep enough in the oxen blockchain to be considered safe to spend.
121  uint64_t accrued_balance; // The unpaid accrued service node rewards currently in the batching database for this currently opened wallet
122  uint64_t accrued_balance_next_payout; // Height that the accrued service node rewards will be paid out
123  bool multisig_import_needed; // True if importing multisig data is needed for returning a correct balance.
124  std::vector<per_subaddress_info> per_subaddress; // Balance information for each subaddress in an account.
125  uint64_t blocks_to_unlock; // The number of blocks remaining for the balance to unlock
126  uint64_t time_to_unlock; // Timestamp of expected unlock
127 
128  KV_MAP_SERIALIZABLE
129  };
130  };

397  // Send oxen to a number of recipients. To preview the transaction fee, set do_not_relay to true and get_tx_metadata to true.
398  // Submit the response using the data in get_tx_metadata in the RPC call, relay_tx.
399  struct TRANSFER : RESTRICTED
400  {
401  static constexpr auto names() { return NAMES("transfer"); }
402 
403  struct request
404  {
405  std::list<wallet::transfer_destination> destinations; // Array of destinations to receive OXEN.
406  uint32_t account_index; // (Optional) Transfer from this account index. (Defaults to 0)
407  std::set<uint32_t> subaddr_indices; // (Optional) Transfer from this set of subaddresses. (Defaults to 0)
408  uint32_t priority; // Set a priority for the transaction. Accepted values are: 1 for unimportant or 5 for blink. (0 and 2-4 are accepted for backwards compatibility and are equivalent to 5)
409  uint64_t unlock_time; // Number of blocks before the oxen can be spent (0 to use the default lock time).
410  std::string payment_id; // (Optional) Random 64-character hex string to identify a transaction.
411  bool get_tx_key; // (Optional) Return the transaction key after sending.
412  bool do_not_relay; // (Optional) If true, the newly created transaction will not be relayed to the oxen network. (Defaults to false)
413  bool get_tx_hex; // Return the transaction as hex string after sending. (Defaults to false)
414  bool get_tx_metadata; // Return the metadata needed to relay the transaction. (Defaults to false)
415 
416  KV_MAP_SERIALIZABLE
417  };
418 
419  struct response
420  {
421  std::string tx_hash; // Publicly searchable transaction hash.
422  std::string tx_key; // Transaction key if get_tx_key is true, otherwise, blank string.
423  uint64_t amount; // Amount transferred for the transaction.
424  uint64_t fee; // Fee charged for the txn.
425  std::string tx_blob; // Raw transaction represented as hex string, if get_tx_hex is true.
426  std::string tx_metadata; // Set of transaction metadata needed to relay this transfer later, if get_tx_metadata is true.
427  std::string multisig_txset; // Set of multisig transactions in the process of being signed (empty for non-multisig).
428  std::string unsigned_txset; // Set of unsigned tx for cold-signing purposes.
429 
430  KV_MAP_SERIALIZABLE
431  };
432  };
